In [5]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.swarmplot(x='abbrev', y='total', data=df, palette='Set2')
plt.xlabel('State Abbreviation')
plt.ylabel('Total Crashes')
plt.title('Swarm Plot of Total Crashes by State')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

<ipython-input-5-45655383b5d9>:2: FutureWarning: Passing `palette` without assigning `hue` is deprecated.
  sns.swarmplot(x='abbrev', y='total', data=df, palette='Set2')

The swarm plot shows individual data points for total crashes by state, giving you a sense of the distribution and density of crash data in each state. It can help identify any outliers or concentration of crash data.

In [6]:
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
sns.kdeplot(df['alcohol'], shade=True, color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Alcohol Level')
plt.ylabel('Density')
plt.title('Kernel Density Estimation (KDE) Plot of Alcohol Levels in Car Crashes')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
